						               													<description>With a beer in one hand and a mallet in the other, the knights of the back garden clash in a dirty duel in which cheap tricks, low blows and bad excuses are the order of the day. Who&amp;rsquo;s getting the beer?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Gameplay in Croquet: A Cardboard Game takes place in turns, with you playing your ball via cards such as &amp;quot;It's Crooked&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Smack in the Arse&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;Almost Straight&amp;quot;. Outside your turn, play as many countermoves you can, whether to annoy the enemy or to optimize your game, countermoves such as &amp;quot;Didn't You Skip Me?&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Ouch! My Foot&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;You Shoot Like a Little Girl&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Description from the first introduction to the game at Fastaval convention:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Croquet is an ancient, noble game where there is only room for the most filthy, sneaky, bullying and vile jerk on top of the podium. The game requires a delicate balancing act between ingenious shots of your own ball in near-impossible zigzag course towards the end pin, and absurd croqueting of your opponents' balls far of the grid. Anything goes. With victory follows the crucial bragging rights - so don't leave your balls at home!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If you like games like RoboRally, Golfmania and Family Business, then croquet - a card board game is just for you.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
